{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Those accused of minor offenses in the Bronx have all but lost their fundamental right to a trial, subjected to such hardship in pursuit of a hearing that it is often easiest to agree to a plea bargain.", "abstract": "Bronx criminal courts are so dysfunctional and backlogged that people accused of misdemeanor offenses like driving with a suspended license have all but lost fundamental right to a trial, and are subjected to such hardship in pursuit of a hearing that it is often easiest to agree to plea bargain; nonprofit group Bronx Defenders is seeking to address problem by helping clients who want to fight their arrests get to trial.", "section_name": "N.Y. / Region", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "William", "role": "reported", "lastname": "GLABERSON", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By WILLIAM GLABERSON", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/01/nyregion/justice-denied-for-misdemeanor-cases-trials-are-elusive.html", "lead_paragraph": "Those accused of minor offenses in the Bronx have all but lost their fundamental right to a trial, subjected to such hardship in pursuit of a hearing that it is often easiest to agree to a plea bargain.", "headline": {"seo": "Justice Denied: For Misdemeanor Cases, Trials Are Elusive", "main": "In Misdemeanor Cases, Long Waits for Elusive Trials", "print_headline": "Even for Minor Crimes in Bronx, No Guarantee of Getting a Trial", "kicker": "Justice Denied"}, "_id": "51811d31cf28d006f100012c", "word_count": "2217", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2013/05/01/nyregion/BRONX2/BRONX2-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2013/05/01/nyregion/BRONX2/BRONX2-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 600, "url": "images/2013/05/01/nyregion/BRONX2/BRONX2-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/05/01/nyregio